    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-04-26T13:23:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-04-26T13:23:00-05:00" n="147"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d147">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/23725: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Nogales</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dyer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nogales, Ariz.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-04-26T11:00:00-07:23">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 26, 1920—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2:44 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Southern Pacific will take on railroad [<hi rend="italic">freight?</hi>] at noon.
                    Telegram was received today saying that Consul General de Negri at New York
                    after protesting to President Carranza about his course toward Sonora without
                    avail tendered his resignation and has proffered his services to Sonora.</p>
                <p>Governor de la Huerta has accepted appointment, under Plan of Agua Prieta<note
                        n="7" xml:id="d147fn7">
                        <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_150">p. 150</ref>.</note> just
                    issued by Calles, as chief executive, civil and military, for States allying
                    themselves with Sonora.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dyer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
